# Cursor AI Rules for Agility CMS Next.js Project

## Project Overview
This is a Next.js 15.3.5 project with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, and Agility CMS integration. The project demonstrates modern web development patterns with CMS-driven content management.

## Core Architecture
- **Framework**: Next.js 15.3.5 with App Router
- **Language**: TypeScript with strict typing
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS file-based approach)
- **CMS**: Agility CMS with @agility/nextjs v15.0.7
- **Animation**: Motion library (Framer Motion alternative)
- **State**: React 19.1.0 with modern hooks
- **Icons**: Heroicons v2 + React Icons
- **Dev Tools**: Turbopack, ESLint, Prettier

## File Structure & Organization
```
src/
├── app/                    # Next.js App Router pages
├── components/            # Reusable UI components
│   ├── agility-components/ # CMS-connected components
│   ├── agility-pages/     # Page-level components
│   └── ui/               # Base UI components
├── lib/                   # Utilities and configurations
│   ├── cms/              # Agility CMS integration
│   ├── types/            # TypeScript definitions
│   └── utils/            # Helper functions
└── styles/               # Global styles and Tailwind
```

## Cursor AI Optimization Patterns

### 1. TypeScript Excellence
- Always use strict typing with `ContentItem<T>` for CMS data
- Define comprehensive interfaces for all content models
- Use discriminated unions for different content types
- Leverage TypeScript's inference capabilities

```typescript
// Example: Strong typing for CMS content
interface IBentoCard {
  title: string;
  description: string;
  image?: ImageField;
  link?: LinkField;
  contentType: 'text' | 'image' | 'link';
}

// Use with ContentItem wrapper
const card: ContentItem<IBentoCard> = await getContentItem<IBentoCard>({...});
```

### 2. Component Architecture
- Follow the "composition over inheritance" principle
- Use React.forwardRef for components that need refs
- Implement proper prop spreading and forwarding
- Use React.memo for performance-critical components

```typescript
// Example: Optimized component structure
const BentoCard = React.memo(React.forwardRef<HTMLDivElement, BentoCardProps>(
  ({ title, description, image, className, ...props }, ref) => {
    return (
      <div ref={ref} className={clsx("bento-card", className)} {...props}>
        {/* Component content */}
      </div>
    );
  }
));
```

### 3. Performance Optimization
- Implement proper loading states and error boundaries
- Use React.Suspense for code splitting
- Optimize images with Next.js Image component
- Implement proper memoization for expensive operations

```typescript
// Example: Performance-optimized data fetching
const useContentItem = <T>(contentID: number, languageCode: string) => {
  return useMemo(async () => {
    return await getContentItem<T>({ contentID, languageCode });
  }, [contentID, languageCode]);
};
```

### 4. Tailwind CSS v4 Best Practices
- Use CSS custom properties for dynamic values
- Leverage CSS file-based approach (no config file)
- Implement responsive design with mobile-first approach
- Use semantic class names and consistent spacing

```css
/* Example: Modern Tailwind v4 approach */
.bento-grid {
  @apply grid gap-6;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(var(--min-width, 300px), 1fr));
}

@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .bento-grid {
    --min-width: 400px;
  }
}
```

## Agility CMS Integration Patterns

### Content Fetching
```typescript
// Single content item
const { fields } = await getContentItem<IContentType>({
  contentID: module.contentid,
  languageCode,
});

// Content lists with pagination
const items = await getContentList<IContentType>({
  referenceName: 'referenceName',
  languageCode,
  take: 20,
  skip: 0,
  sort: 'sortOrder',
  filter: 'status[eq]Published'
});

// Nested content relationships
const { fields: { nestedRef } } = await getContentItem<IParentType>({...});
const nestedItems = await getContentList<INestedType>({
  referenceName: nestedRef.referencename,
  languageCode
});
```

### Component Props Interface
```typescript
interface UnloadedModuleProps {
  module: {
    contentid: number;
    modulename: string;
    [key: string]: any;
  };
  languageCode: string;
  sitemapNode?: SitemapNode;
}
```

### CMS Field Attributes
```typescript
// Add these attributes for Agility CMS inline editing
<div data-agility-component={contentID}>
  <h2 data-agility-field="title">{fields.title}</h2>
  <div data-agility-field="description">{fields.description}</div>
</div>
```

## Animation & Motion Patterns

### Staggered Animations
```typescript
// Calculate delays for grid items
const getStaggerDelay = (index: number, baseDelay: number = 0.1) => {
  return index * baseDelay;
};

// Use in Motion components
<Motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  transition={{ delay: getStaggerDelay(index) }}
>
  {content}
</Motion.div>
```

### Responsive Animation
```typescript
// Conditional animations based on viewport
const isMobile = useMediaQuery('(max-width: 768px)');

const animationVariants = {
  initial: { opacity: 0, y: isMobile ? 10 : 20 },
  animate: { opacity: 1, y: 0 }
};
```

## Error Handling & Validation

### Content Validation
```typescript
// Validate required CMS fields
const validateContent = (fields: any): fields is IContentType => {
  return fields.title && fields.description;
};

// Use in components
if (!validateContent(fields)) {
  return <div>Content not available</div>;
}
```

### Error Boundaries
```typescript
// Implement error boundaries for CMS components
class CMSErrorBoundary extends React.Component {
  // Error boundary implementation
}
```

